Yeah....beauty of a day. Awesome flight in and out and seeing Anishanabi Lodge on the way back was pretty cool too. I'm pretty sure Jason and I would jump on that plane again in about a nanosecond. Now, if I could only get him to remember his rainsuit on those type of trips.. PjShorthorn
Think jason is ready for that.communicate often on msg with him and frank.

Want to go to Amisk Lake in Canada in June. Not sure if it will work out though.
135 days to the opener at O'Sullivans Rainbow.
156 days until St Joe!

211 days until we go back to Pipestone Lake to hunt trophy walleyes for a week. I'm also taking the canoe, because we're going to spend an additional 3 days in the Nestor Falls and Kenora area fishing some lake trout, smallmouth, and northern pike on some out of the way lakes that we've discovered in the past couple years. So, it's going to be a 10-day trip. Already counting down the days. (and remembering to include the Leap Year when doing so) "Jackpot" John Schroeder
